3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Signs Your Heater Needs a Tune-Up<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>At Medley Heating, Air Conditioning &amp; Plumbing, we recommend that you schedule at least one heating system tune-up service each year. The best time to schedule your tune-up is before the coldest months of the year begin, so either in early autumn or even in the summer.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>That being said, there are some signs that indicate your heater could use an inspection, cleaning, and tune-up service. If you notice any of these signs, reach out to Medley Heating, Air Conditioning &amp; Plumbing right away to learn how we can help you get the most out of your heating system.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Some of the most common signs that your heating system needs a tune-up include:&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Uneven heating or cool spots throughout your home\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Vents that only blow cool or lukewarm air\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Unusual noises, such as banging or clanking\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.callmedley.com\/indoor-air-quality\/thermostats\/\">Thermostat issues<\/a>, such as having to constantly turn the thermostat up<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Strange and unpleasant odors coming from the heater<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Frequent cycling (turning on and off)\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>A heater that stays on for too long\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Excessive and\/or visible wear and tear\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If your heating system is especially old\u2014about 15 to 20 years old or older\u2014it may be worthwhile to consider replacing it altogether. If you choose to go this route, turn to Medley Heating, Air Conditioning &amp; Plumbing for help with&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/www.callmedley.com\/heating\/heating-system-installation\/\">new heating system installation<\/a>. We can help you find the right solution for your home.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Commonly Asked Questions<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What types of heating systems do you service?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We service all types of heating systems, including gas furnaces, electric furnaces, heat pumps, central heaters, and ductless mini-splits.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">When is the best time to schedule a heating system tune-up?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The best time to schedule a heating system tune-up is before the coldest months of the year begin, so either in early autumn or even in the summer.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Should I consider replacing my old heating system?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If your heating system is 15 to 20 years old or older, it may be worthwhile to consider replacing it. We can help you with new heating system installation and find the right solution for your home.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Benefits of Regular Heating System Maintenance<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Having your heating system regularly maintained by a professional HVAC technician offers many benefits. Not only can it allow you to enjoy a more comfortable home, but it can also save you considerable money\u2014both now and in the future.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Some of the many benefits of routine heating system maintenance include:&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Better Performance:\u00a0<\/strong>A regularly maintained system will work better, meaning you\u2019ll enjoy a warmer, more comfortable home with even heating throughout.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Fewer System Breakdowns:<\/strong>\u00a0Regular tune-ups allow our technicians to catch and address minor issues before they have the chance to develop into larger, more serious problems.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Increased Lifespan:<\/strong>\u00a0By addressing routine wear and tear with annual maintenance, you can significantly extend the lifespan of your heating system.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Improved Air Quality:\u00a0<\/strong>Routine heating maintenance can improve the air quality inside your home, reducing allergens, dust, pollen, bacteria, and other harmful pollutants.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Greater Energy Efficiency:<\/strong>\u00a0A well-cared-for heating system is also an efficient system. Regular tune-ups can improve energy efficiency\u2014and reduce your energy costs.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Long-Term Cost Savings:\u00a0<\/strong>By reducing wear and tear, decreasing the risk of breakdowns, and improving energy efficiency, heating maintenance allows for considerable long-term savings.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Improved Safety:\u00a0<\/strong>Certain heating system problems can be hazardous to your health and the safety of your family. Regular maintenance helps improve the safety of your system.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Increased Reliability:\u00a0<\/strong>By taking the time to ensure that your heating system is working well, you won\u2019t have to worry about problems or breakdowns when you need your heater the most.\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>There are many reasons to schedule a routine heating system tune-up in Carrollton or any of the nearby areas. If you are interested in booking an appointment with Medley Heating, Air Conditioning &amp; Plumbing, just reach out to our friendly and professional team. We are happy to answer any questions you may have and help you get set up with your tune-up service today.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.callmedley.com\/filters\/\"><strong>See the filter options we have available.<\/strong><\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Experience the Medley Heating, Air Conditioning &amp; Plumbing Difference Today!<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Service You Can Trust<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We are proud to serve residents of Carrollton, Texas and the surrounding areas, offering high-quality&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/www.callmedley.com\/heating\/\">heating services<\/a>&nbsp;backed by our numerous service guarantees. We genuinely care about you and you